HEADWORD: Parthenope
<hw>Par*then"o*pe</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r*th⟦ecr⟧n"⟦osl⟧*p⟦emac⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the name of a Siren, fr. Gr.
<grk>Parqeno`ph</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gr. Myth.)</fld>
<def>One of the Sirens, who threw herself into the sea, in despair at
not being able to beguile <persfn>Ulysses</persfn> by her
songs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the asteroids between Mars and Jupiter,
discovered by <person>M. de Gasparis</person> in 1850.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parthian</ent>⟦br⟧
